^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I don't recommend you play this convention, but let me discuss "Puppet Stayman" which many experts play over 2NT. The reason they play it is it allows you to discover if the 2NT bidder has either a 4-card major or 5-card major. In normal setting (not paying Puppet Stayman) the correct bid by Liza is 3N.|
PG| ***** 2 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|On this hand, I don't think, even were we playing it, Liza should bid it with 4-3-3-3 distribution because it is likely, even if we have an 8-card major suit fit, NT will play as well, and is a 9-trick contract rather than a 10-trick contract.|
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|For the sake of the lesson, however, let us assume Liza wanted to find out if I had a 5-card major so we could play in a 5-3 fit. I will show you how puppet works. So Liza bid 3@C and I will walk you  through it.|mb|3C|
pg| ***** 4 ***** |


mb|p|NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If we were playing Puppet Stayman: 
I bid that major—3@H or 3@S if I have a five-card major
I bid 3@D if I have 1 or 2 four-card majors 
I bid 3NT if I have neither.|
