%%%http://web2.acbl.org/documentLibrary/play/Commonly_Used_Conventions/puppetstayman.pdf

ht|g|AT|^B@2Puppet Stayman is a version of Stayman used in response to a 2NT opening bid. Puppet Stayman also applies when it goes 2@C-P-2@D-P-2N-P-3@C. In general, whatever you play over a 2N opener, you also play over when opener bids 2@C and then rebids 2N. Usually, 2NT opener promises a balanced hand with 20 to 21 high-card points—with or without 5-card majors. Therefore, a 5-3 major suit fit could be missed if responder has only 3-card in the suit which opener has 5-cards. Puppet Stayman is intended to remedy that problem. Let us look at  a few examples. In all examples the opponents are silent.|
